# test-client-design-system — AI Coding Instructions
# Generated by Guing v0.0.1 on 2026-04-19T20:05:46.754Z
# Base UI library: Material UI (mui)

## Package import
Always import from `test-client-design-system` — NEVER from the underlying library directly:
```tsx
import { Button, vars } from 'test-client-design-system';
import 'test-client-design-system/src/design-tokens/tokens.css';
```

## Design Token Rules
- NEVER hardcode hex colors — use CSS variables or `vars` references
- NEVER hardcode font sizes or spacing values
- TypeScript access: `import { designTokens, vars } from 'test-client-design-system'`

## vars.* shape (typed CSS-variable references)
- vars.color           — brand500, actionPrimary, actionSecondary, success500, warning500, danger500, background, surface, textMain, textMuted, borderDivider
- vars.colorToken      — surfaceElavateL1, surfaceElavateL2, surfaceBase, surfaceBold100, surfaceBold200, backgroundWhiteBase, backgroundBlackBase, surfaceBold300, backgroundNeutralSubtle400, backgroundNeutralSubtle300, backgroundNeutralSubtle200, backgroundNeutralSubtle100 … (277 total)
- vars.radius          — small, medium, large, round
- vars.radiusToken     — borderRadiusNone, borderRadiusXs, borderRadiusSm, borderRadiusMd, borderRadiusLg, borderRadiusXl, borderRadius2xl, borderRadius3xl … (13)
- vars.font            — h1Regular, h1Bold, h2Regular, h2Bold, h3Regular, h3Bold, h4Regular, h4Bold (each: .family .size .weight .lineHeight)
- vars.spacing         — headingH2LetterSpacing, headingH2ParagaphSpacing, headingH1LetterSpacing, headingH1ParagaphSpacing, headingH4LetterSpacing, headingH4ParagaphSpacing, headingH3LetterSpacing, headingH3ParagaphSpacing, bodyLgLetterSpacing, bodyLgParagaphSpacing, bodySmLetterSpacing, bodySmParagaphSpacing, bodyMdLetterSpacing, bodyMdParagaphSpacing, bodyXsLetterSpacing, bodyXsParagaphSpacing, headingH5LetterSpacing, headingH5ParagaphSpacing, bodyXxsLetterSpacing, bodyXxsParagaphSpacing
- vars.size            — fontWeightRegular400, dimensionNull, dimension4025Rem, dimension60375Rem, dimension805Rem, dimension100625Rem, dimension12075Rem, dimension140875Rem
- vars.shadow          — small, medium, large, inner
- vars.gradient        — miscSocialRing

Usage example:
```tsx
import { vars } from 'test-client-design-system';
<Box sx={{ backgroundColor: vars.color.actionPrimary, borderRadius: vars.radius.medium }} />
```

## Namespace Component API
All Figma-derived components are exported as namespace objects.
Import and use them like this:
```tsx
import { Blurs, Borders, Colors, Elevations, Gaps, Grids, Icons, Injection, Model, Opacity, Radius, Shadows, Sizes, Text, Token, Typography, Welcome, Button (Secondary) } from 'test-client-design-system';

<Blurs.default onClick={fn} isLoading={false} />
<Borders.default onClick={fn} isLoading={false} />
<Colors.default onClick={fn} isLoading={false} />
<Elevations.default onClick={fn} isLoading={false} />
<Gaps.default onClick={fn} isLoading={false} />
<Grids.default onClick={fn} isLoading={false} />
<Icons.default onClick={fn} isLoading={false} />
<Injection.View onClick={fn} isLoading={false} />
<Model.Map onClick={fn} isLoading={false} />
<Opacity.default onClick={fn} isLoading={false} />
<Radius.default onClick={fn} isLoading={false} />
<Shadows.default onClick={fn} isLoading={false} />
<Sizes.default onClick={fn} isLoading={false} />
<Text.default onClick={fn} isLoading={false} />
<Token.MapView onClick={fn} isLoading={false} />
<Typography.default onClick={fn} isLoading={false} />
<Welcome.default onClick={fn} isLoading={false} />
<Button (Secondary).default onClick={fn} isLoading={false} />
```

### Standard props (every AI-generated component accepts these)
- `onClick?: () => void` — click handler
- `onHover?: () => void` — mouse-enter handler
- `isDisabled?: boolean` — disables the component
- `isLoading?: boolean` — shows a spinner; disables interaction
- `children?: React.ReactNode` — content slot
- `sx?: Record<string, unknown>` — style overrides (spread last; developer wins)
- `className?: string` — class overrides

